comments.content: You might want to contact the deviantart user. They probably know what font they used.

I actually spent a fair amount of time looking for this at MyFonts and Dafont with no luck. I am having trouble deciding what category or keyword would best describe it. To me this looks like the work of a professional type designer, but it is not familiar enough, except as a general ’fun’ style, to know where to look. I am looking again, but I hope someone answers this.

- Mike Yanega

If you are willing to consider fonts with a similar feeling, I have written down a few I’ve seen at MyFonts so far: Good Eatin, Houndcats, Framistat and [ITC Eborg](http://web.archive.org/web/20090503105829/http:/new.myfonts.com/fonts/itc/eborg-itc/).

I made a link for the last one, because I am an Eborg fan, and use it a lot myself.

- Mike Yanega
